criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  adult patients, >=18 years of age;

          -  chronic renal anemia;

          -  regular hemodialysis with the same schedule of dialysis for >=12 weeks;

          -  maintenance therapy with subcutaneous epoetin alfa at the same administration interval
             for 4 weeks.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  transfusion of red blood cells during previous 2 months;

          -  poorly controlled hypertension requiring interruption of epoetin alfa in previous 6
             months;

          -  acute or chronic bleeding;

          -  active malignant disease (except non-melanoma skin cancer).
